content: <?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>  <reference anchor='RFC7464'>  <front> <title>JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) Text Sequences</title> <author initials='N.' surname='Williams' fullname='N. Williams'> <organization /></author> <date year='2015' month='February' /> <abstract> <t>This document describes the JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) text sequence format and associated media type "application/json-seq".  A JSON text sequence consists of any number of JSON texts, all encoded in UTF-8, each prefixed by an ASCII Record Separator (0x1E), and each ending with an ASCII Line Feed character (0x0A).</t></abstract></front>  <seriesInfo name='RFC' value='7464' /> <format type='TXT' octets='16132' target='http://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc7464.txt' /> </reference>
